DruCipher writes "CNet.co.uk is running a very funny article about Andrew
Lim, the resident mobile phone reviewer, trying to [0]live without all
his favorite gadgets. The article sees Andrew try to survive without a
mobile phone, a computer, an MP3 player and a TV. At the end of his
technology detox he feels more relaxed without all his gadgets but cracks
after a few days, 'Like all proper detoxes, though, my zen-like calm
didn't last for long. Once I'd finished my gadget starvation, I was
straight back to the tech binging. A remote control gun you say? Yes
please!'"

